01:29:57.180 --> 01:30:05.020
divided by pl.call N.sum over condition.

01:30:06.219 --> 01:30:12.939
So this is kind of like, this is like using a group by with mutate in dplyr.

01:30:13.500 --> 01:30:15.180
Or the dot group by argument.

01:30:17.739 --> 01:30:25.500
Over, we're saying, sum and within, sorry, my little zoom bars in the way.

01:30:26.140 --> 01:30:27.739
Sum N within each condition.

01:30:28.540 --> 01:30:33.500
And return that sum for that condition for each of the values in that condition.

